        "title": "Guard compaction reserve against prompt starvation",
        "body": "## Summary\n- cap Pi compaction reserve to at most half of the resolved context window\n- lower an already-too-large reserve during Pi settings application instead of preserving prompt starvation\n- make the context-overflow recovery hint warn when the configured reserve is too high for the model window\n\n## Background\nA Telegram session on a 120k-token model had `agents.defaults.compaction.reserveTokensFloor=70000`. After compaction, the prompt still needed about 54k tokens, but the 70k reserve left only 50k input budget, so every retry overflowed and the user-facing recovery hint incorrectly suggested increasing the reserve.\n\n## Test plan\n- `node scripts/test-projects.mjs src/agents/pi-settings.test.ts src/auto-reply/reply/agent-runner-execution.test.ts`\n",
